##Key concepts

Identity-Aware Proxy (IAP) Tunneling

-- instead of opening port 22 to the whole internet IAP acts like a secure "slide door"
It checks my google identity (IAM) and then wraps my SSH traffic in an encrypted tunnel and 
sends it to the VM theough googles internal network

Cloud Nat (Network Address Translation)

--a protocol that allows a private VM with no public ip address to communicate to the inernet
but nothing from outside the defualt gate can initate a communication back

Network Tags 

-- a sort of stamp that tells the VPC firewall to apply rthese securtiy 
rules associated with the tag(stamp) speciffally to this machine


IAP IP Range (35.235.240.0/20) 

a specific static range or ip addresses owned by Google needed 
to all the IAP tunnel to pass though the network prrimeter 

